lzh_formatted:
  title: 放鴈
  author: 權思復
  language: lzh
  text: 雲漢猶堪任意飛。稻田胡自蹈危機。從今去向冥冥外。只要全身勿要肥。
korean:
  title: 방안
  author: 권사복
  language: kor
  text: |-
    높은 하늘에 오히려 마음대로 날으면서
    어찌하여 벼밭의 위험함을 스스로 밟는가
    지금부터는 저 아득한 밖으로 가서
    다만 몸 하나만 보전하고 살찌기를 구하지 말라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_1150&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Releasing the Geese
  author: Kwon Sa-bok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The vast sky still permits you to soar as you please—
    why then do you tread the perils of the rice fields?
    From this day forth, fly toward that distant boundless realm.
    Seek only to preserve your life; abandon the pursuit of fatness.
  footnotes:
    - The poem appears to be an allegory addressing the reader to abandon worldly pursuits and dangers in favor of spiritual freedom and survival.
    - The contrast between 'fatness' (accumulation of wealth or status) and mere survival suggests a Buddhist or Taoist influence encouraging renunciation of material excess.
